gomodel:SYNGO_2151  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Postsynaptic Stx-3 KD in vivo Does Not Alter Basal Synaptic Transmission or Constitutive Recycling\"\n- Subcellular localization of STX3 observed in dendrites using structured illumination microscopy: \"Stx-3 was often found adjacent to PSD-95 puncta, consistent with recent studies using immunogold labeling of syntaxins in hippocampal slices and cultured neurons (J.H. Tao-Cheng et al., 2012, Soc. Neurosci., abstract).\". Experimental description: \"Dissociated hippocampal cultures were prepared from newborn C57BL/6 mice as previously described...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2151" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
